    {
      "id": "1c3a9512d275822fb1627fc842eca0f3eb959e13",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-15 16:23:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nSorry for the delay in inspecting this. If you find your patches are not being inspected or landed in a timely manner, please ping people in the patch or in Skype to get them moving. \n\nI think the reason they were being excluded is because there are separate stats for individual MDS_REINT operations (e.g. mds_rename, mds_setattr, etc) that were added. Similarly, individual DLM lock types were added (e.g. ldlm_ibits_lock).\n\nSee /proc/fs/lustre/mdt/MDS/mds/stats for example. I think it would be more useful to also account for the individual operations in the MDC and OSC stats rather than just MDS_REINT and LDLM_ENQUEUE. With the current patch this would add double accounting on the server side. \n\n\nIt might also be useful to have a test if these RPCs are being accounted for. There are already some tests for the server side stats, but I'm not sure about the client stats.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
